g.text: BOOST: By default, built-in battery charger on nRFNANO charges at 100mA max.
If you solder the bridge together it will increase the max charging to 500mA.
BAT-TS: This solder bridge is provided to provide safer charging experience.
Desolder the resistor marked in purple and solder temperature sensor to BAT-TS solder bridge.
See details in datasheet of BQ24075RGTT.
3.3V: 3.3V (500mA max.) output which can be controlled with P0.13.
When P0.13 is set low, it will shut the power off to 3.3V pin.
This can be used to control power of external components.
